# DTC economics are fundamentally superior to wholesale — when scaled correctly
@type: stat_callout

@stat: 2.1× | Higher Customer LTV | DTC vs. wholesale-acquired customers at 36 months
@stat: 58% | Gross Margin on DTC | Vs. 34% through retail wholesale channel
@stat: 3.4× | Repeat Purchase Rate | For DTC subscription customers vs. one-time buyers

@exhibit: Exhibit 1 — DTC vs. Wholesale Economics
@source: BCG DTC Consumer Benchmark, N=85 brands $50M–$1B revenue, 2024

@notes: The margin differential is the strategic imperative. At $500M DTC revenue vs. equivalent wholesale revenue, the gross margin difference is $120M annually.

