# Building a $500M DTC business requires three capability investments
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Technology Stack
  - Headless commerce platform enabling sub-2s load times
  - CDP unifying digital, in-store, and loyalty data
  - Personalization engine for email, site, and paid media
  - First-party analytics replacing cookie-dependent attribution

@col:
  ## Brand and Content Engine
  - In-house content studio producing 40+ assets/week
  - Community platform converting buyers to advocates
  - Creator partnership program (mid-tier, high authenticity)
  - UGC strategy: reviews, social proof, community content

@notes: Most brands underinvest in content relative to media spend. The winning formula is 70/30 — 70% earned/owned content driving 30% paid amplification.

---

# DTC Revenue Scales to $500M Through Three Compounding Growth Phases
@type: timeline

@step: 2025 | Foundation ($165M → $220M) | Platform migration, CDP launch, subscription program relaunch
@step: 2026 | Acceleration ($220M → $340M) | Social commerce expansion, creator network, international test
@step: 2027 | Scale ($340M → $430M) | App launch, loyalty 2.0, Amazon channel optimization
@step: 2028 | Target ($430M → $500M) | International rollout, B2B DTC program, brand extensions

@source: BCG growth model based on comparable DTC brand trajectories, 2024

@notes: The 2025 foundation year is non-negotiable. Trying to accelerate without the technology stack produces short-term revenue that cannot sustain.

